Name: Swan and Marclaren
Author: Julian Davison
Description: Swan & Maclaren were one of the main architectural practices working in Singapore from their foundation in 1892 through to independence in 1965. As such, the history of Singapore architecture, during that period, is very much the history of Swan & Maclaren.

Name: Git: The Power of Passion and Perseverance
Author: Angela Duckworth
Description: In this instant New York Times bestseller, Angela Duckworth shows anyone striving to succeed that the secret to outstanding achievement is not talent, but a special blend of passion and persistence she calls "grit." "Inspiration for non-geniuses everywhere" (People).

Name: The Ride of a Lifetime
Author: Robert Iger
Description: he CEO of Disney, one of Time's most influential people of 2019, shares the ideas and values he embraced to reinvent one of the most beloved companies in the world and inspire the people who bring the magic to life. Robert Iger became CEO of The Walt Disney Company in 2005, during a difficult time.

Name: The Montessori Toddler
Author: Simone Davies
Description: It’s time to change the way we see toddlers. Using the principles developed by the educator Dr. Maria Montessori, Simone Davies shows how to turn life with a “terrible two” into a mutually rich and rewarding time of curiosity, learning, respect, and discovery.

Name: Zero to One: Notes on Start Ups
Author: Blake Masters
Description: The next Larry Page or Sergey Brin won't make a search engine. If you are copying these guys, you aren't learning from them.

Name: Nightfall: 6
Author: Shannon Messenger
Description: A New York Times bestselling series A USA TODAY bestselling series A California Young Reader Medal-winning series Sophie and her friends face battles unlike anything they've seen before in this thrilling sixth book of the New York Times and USA TODAY bestselling Keeper of the Lost Cities series.

Name: The Heros of Olympus Set
Author: Rick Riordan
Description: All five books in the Heroes of Olympus saga--in a paperback boxed set of heroic proportions. From The Lost Hero to the Blood of Olympus, this collection of Rick Riordan's mega-bestselling series will be a go-to gift for readers who have finished the Percy Jackson and the Olympians books.

Name: Brain Quest WorkBook
Author: Lisa Trumbauer
Description: It’s fun to be smart! Loved by kids, teacher approved, and parent trusted, Brain Quest Kindergarten Workbook reviews and reinforces what kids are learning in the classroom in an instantly engaging, entertaining way.

Name: Autumn Baking
Author: Chuah Chiew See
Description: Autumn baking - Natural Yeast is a baking book with recipes that use only natural yeast. The book cover from how to build your own natural yeast,method of hand mix and dozen of recipes from classic sourdough to sweet bread and other Asian bakes.

Name: A Guest in the Jungle
Author: James Poister
Description: It is high noon in the Amazon, and Whitehill is lost. In his Brooks Brothers pants, this lawyer from the Midwest is easily the best-dressed man in the jungle. Unfortunately, he's no Indiana Jones.

Name: Beyond the Shadow of Night
Author: Ray Kingfisher
Description: Ukraine, 1923. On a small farm, two boys are born within days of each other, both Ukrainian, one Jewish. Mykhail and Asher grow up inseparable, together finding friendship, adventure and escape from the harshness of Russian rule.

Name: Coco Chanel
Author: Megan Hess
Description: Coco Chanel: The Illustrated World of a Fashion Icon is an illustrated biography of Coco's Chanel's life from the internationally reknown illustrator and author, Megan Hess.

Name: The Megic Trap
Author: MS Jacqueline Davies
Description: Jessie and Evan Treski have waged a lemonade war, sought justice in a class trial, unmasked a bell thief, and stood at opposite ends over the right to keep secrets.

Name: Magnum Streetwise
Author: Stephen McLaren
Description: Ambitious in scope, democratic in nature, Magnum Streetwise is an unmissable tour through the photographs and practices that have helped define what street photography is and can be.

Name: True Love
Author: Jennifer Lopez
Description: In Jennifer Lopez's first ever book, True Love, she explores one of her life's most defining periods--the transformative two-year journey of how, as an artist and a mother, she confronted her greatest challenges, identified her biggest fears, and ultimately emerged a stronger person than she's ever been.

Name: Here We Are
Author: Oliver Jeffers
Description: Oliver Jeffers, arguably the most influential creator of picture books today, offers a rare personal look inside his own hopes and wishes for his child--and in doing so gifts children and parents everywhere with a gently sweet and humorous missive about our world and those who call it home.

Name: Hop on Pop
Author: Dr. Seuss
Description: A condensed, board-book version of the classic best-seller introduces the youngest readers to the wonderful world of Seussian word play.

Name: The Cold War
Author: John Lewis Gaddis
Description: A brilliantly arresting historical work, John Lewis Gaddis's The Cold War takes us as never before to the time when the world stood on the brink of destruction.

Name: Atomic Habits
Author: James Clear
Description: Tiny Changes, Remarkable Results No matter your goals, Atomic Habits offers a proven framework for improving—every day.

Name: Untamed
Author: Glennon Doyle
Description: There is a voice of longing inside each woman. We strive so mightily to be good: good partners, daughters, mothers, employees, and friends.

Name: The Lemonade Crime
Author: Ms Jacqueline Davies
Description: Following the laws of our legal system, Evan and Jessie's fourth grade class concocts a courtroom on the playground, putting Scott Spencer, alleged thief, on trial.

Name: How To be an Antiracist
Author: Ibram
Description: it feels like a light switch being flicked on' OWEN JONES Not being racist is not enough.

Name: Wine Folly
Author: Madeline Puckette
Description: Wine Folly became a sensation for its inventive, easy-to-digest approach to learning about wine.

Name: High Output Management
Author: Andrew S.Grove
Description: The essential skill of creating and maintaining new businesses—the art of the entrepreneur—can be summed up in a single word: managing.
